"v.涉足，浅赏 【英】 v. 涉足，浅赏(to do something superficially, not seriously) 【考】 反义词：dedicate(致 力); devote(投身于) 【记】 不要和babble(说蠢话 )相混 【例】 to dabble in politics v. 涉足; 涉猎(草率而且没有严肃目的地做某件事) 【记】总是dabble的人对专业知识了解不深, 只会babble(v 说蠢话)因为三心二double意, 所以dabble 【类】martinet: leniency = dabbler: dedication严格的人不宽大 = 业余学者不奉献 【反】dedicate = devote(vt 投入于; 献身); specialize(vi 专攻); dabbler(n 初学者)－specialist/ dedicate professional(n 专家) 【记】源自dab 少量, 轻拍,轻擦,涂；近dip 浸，p=b 中间是元音；音：打波，打ball，我们打球只是打着玩；打波从字面看是用手击打水波的意思；有paddle 玩水的意思 【相关】dab轻拍, daub 涂抹, dub 轻点, paddle玩水，stab 刺伤 dabble (v.)  1550s, probably a frequentative of dab. Original meaning was ""wet by splashing;"" modern figurative sense of ""do superficially"" first recorded 1620s. Related: Dabbled; dabbling. An Ellen Dablewife is in the Lancashire Inquests from 1336."
